## DTI Topology Fidelity Violation (Discovered 2026-04-25)
================================================================================

### Problem
The generated build output does NOT match the topology described in
soc_dti_noc_topo. The topology description specifies 4 switches (sw0/sw1/sw2/sw3)
+ buffer + async bridge + tcu_tniu, but the generator implements 7 switches
with completely different naming (dti_sw_left3, dti_sw_left_dsp0, ...).

### Current Gen Output
  dti_sw_left3       dti_sw_left_dsp1    dti_sw_right4       dti_sw_root
  dti_sw_left_dsp0   dti_sw_left_noc1    dti_sw_right_noc0

### Topology Described
  dsp ss0~5 iniu  -> sw0 ch0~5
  cpu~mipi iniu   -> sw1 ch0~4
  gpu~dp iniu     -> sw2 ch0~3 -> dti buffer -> dti async bridge slv
  dti async bridge mst -> sw3 ch2
  sw0 -> sw3 ch0
  sw1 -> sw3 ch1
  sw3 -> tcu tniu

### Root Cause
  The DtiTemplate.py and DtiTreeTopo.py were written for an OLD topology
  (left/right tree with 7 switches) and were never updated to reflect the
  soc_dti_noc_topo description. The generator code and topology description
  have diverged completely.

### Resolution Required
  - Rewrite DtiTemplate.py switch configs to match sw0/sw1/sw2/sw3 naming
  - Rewrite DtiTreeTopo.py connections to match soc_dti_noc_topo
  - Verify build output directories match described switch names
  - This is a P0 item that must be fixed before DTI can be considered compliant.

